ng to be discovered. It will be of great value to those studying literary history, medieval studies, cultural geography, gender studies, Jewish studies and book history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literatureyMiddle English, 1100-1500xHistory and criticism. 0aLatin literature, Medieval and modernzEnglandxHistory and criticism. 0aManuscripts, MedievalzEnglandzHereford. 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Norman literature.  aEnglish literary history.  aHarley 2253.  aMiddle English literature.  acultural geography.  adevotional literature.  aliterary geography.  aregionalism in literature.  athe Harley Lyrics.  athe medieval miscellany.1 aBirkholz, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614041840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526140418423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526140418/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles